<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Top place - fantastic location and bargain price!! Just back from a stay here last week (Oct 4th - 6th) and found it to be an excellent hotel. We caught the Aerobus from the airport direct to the Placya Catalunya (only 3.75 euros each) and then it's a 5 miute walk down the Ramblas to the hotel on your left. We arrived around 11am but our room wasn't yet ready so we left our bags in a secure room and went out for a drink. Came back and checked into our room and was delighted to see it was even better than the one in the photo. Yes it was small but for the price and location it was ideal. It must have been recently refurbished as it was all dark brown wood oriental style. Bathroom was also spotless.As stated the location is fantastic, we sat at the hotel bar upstairs on the balcony overlooking the main drag of the Ramblas where we were able to watch the street performers and just generally people watch for hours. The beer in the bar was huge, we asked for a medium and it was in a large fish-bowl glass.I would highly recommend this hotel to anyone purely for the cost and location. It said 1 star on the door as we went in but I have stopped in much worse 3 star hotels in the past.Only downsides were the fact we asked if breakfast was included and were told it was so we had it both days (continental) and were then charge 6EUR each per day. Had we known it was to be charged we would have probably gone elsewhere.Other is that my wifes glasses went walkabout after we left them in the room. There is a safe available in the room but you must pay extra for it so it may be our fault for not doing that but then again would you really put a pair of specs in there?The hotel were good about it and asked the maids/cleaning firm etc but they couldn't find them. Annoying yes but it wouldn't make me not recommend this hotel.Barcelona is one of the best places i've ever been!! Nou Camp tour is fantastic. 
<Date>Oct 11, 2004
