<Author>Online-Buy
<Content>Barcelona - Hotel Husa Internacional We stayed here for 2 nights in March 2004. Our room was very clean with TV, but had old funiture. We paid 100 Euro for a double room without breakfast. At night it is very noisy, but for two days it's ok. The Hotel is located right on the Ramblas and only a 10 minute walk away from the Place de Catalunya und the Harbor, a Metro station is in front of the Hotel (singel ticket is 1.10 Euro) near by is the Gothic Quarter. To see Barcelona, buy a ticket for the Tourist Bus (16 Euro per Person) it's a hop-on-hop-off trip and brings you to all the interesting places in Barcelona. If you want to see the Miro Museum, it is closed on Mondays. 
