<Content>Hotel Internacional on the Ramblas We stayed here for 3 nights in July, 2002. The hotel lobby is very pretty, but that's pretty much the extent of the hotel. Our room was tiny (by European standards) and very moderatlely decorated. The rooms are not air-conditioned - in July air-conditioning is a must. We had to leave the windows open to get some air and it was extremely noisy during the wee hours of the night. We felt it was pretty pricey $95 USD for the accomodations. Breakfast was nothing to wright home about, but served in a nice room overlooking the Ramblas. The location of the hotel is great. On the Ramblas, near lot's of the Gothic Quarter attractions and restaurants. If you don't mind the noise, make sure to request a room with a balcony overlooking the street. Great for people watching.Have fun, Barcelona is a terrrific city. 
